ld should be scheduled for check-ups once every six months. However, your dentist may recommend more visits depending on your child\'s personal oral health.\r\n<h5>At what age should I take my child for his first dental check-up?</h5>\r\nThe American Academy of Pediatric Dentistry suggests that a child visits the dentist no later than his first birthday. A child should be examined by the dentist as soon as his first tooth erupts, usually between six to twelve months.'),
