(104,3,'2015-02-15 14:40:32','2015-02-15 11:40:32','<h6>Specialist Orthodontist, Sweden\r\nUmm Suqeim Clinic</h6>\r\n<div class=\"justext\">\r\n\r\nDr. Lina completed her postgraduate training in Orthodontics at Karolinska Institutet, Sweden, in 1997, after earning her DDS from the University of Athens, Greece, in 1993.\r\n\r\nHer academic background and vast experience gained over the past twenty years have given her the right skills in planning effective orthodontic treatments for both children and adults, applying a variety of treatments - such as the Damon System that requires shorter treatment time, Invisalign and other aesthetic treatments, depending on the needs of each patient. She works closely with the implant, oral surgery and restorative teams to tailor treatments for patients needing multi-disciplinary care.\r\n\r\nShe has published at the American Journal of Orthodontics and Dentofacial Orthopedics and is very passionate about continuous education and development. \"I believe this learning process is something that should never cease no matter what your experience or background is. I am therefore always open to new ideas and practices.\"\r\n\r\nDr. Lina is registered with the General Dental Council in the United Kingdom as a Specialist Orthodontist. She holds professional licenses in Dubai, Greece and the UK. She is a member of the World Federation of Orthodontists, American Association of Orthodontists, the Hellenic Orthodontic Society and the Greek Association for Orthodontic Study and Research.\r\n\r\nShe speaks English, Greek, French and basic Swedish.\r\n\r\n</div>','Dr. Lina Stavroula Papika','','inherit','open','open','','102-revision-v1','','','2015-02-15 14:40:32','2015-02-15 11:40:32','',102,'http://demo2.saitobaza.ru/102-revision-v1.htm',0,'revision','',0),
(105,3,'2015-02-15 14:41:15','2015-02-15 11:41:15','<h6>DDS, Dr. Med. Sci (Hons), Denmark\r\nUmm Suqeim Clinic</h6>\r\n<div class=\"justext\">\r\n\r\nSteen Sindet-Pedersen received his dental degree from the University of Aarhus (Denmark) in 1979. He pursued further studies and completed his specialist training as Oral Maxillofacial Surgeon in 1985, and earned his Doctorate in Medical Science (Hons) in 1991 from the same university.\r\n\r\nHe was the Acting Head of the Department of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery, Aarhus University Hospital from 1989 to 1993. He was appointed lifelong Professor in Oral Maxillofacial Surgery by Queen Margaret of Denmark in 1993. He was also a visiting professor of the Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery Department at the University of Texas in Houston, USA from 1989 to 1998, and was appointed the first professor of Oral and Maxillofacial Implantology in Europe at Eastman Dental Institute, University College London in 1998. Carrying out dental implant and bone grafting procedures, Dr. Steen was also a visiting surgeon at the Zahnklinik Rennbahn AG in Basel, Switzerland from 1995 to 2011.\r\n\r\nDr. Steen has also contributed largely in the biotechnology industry. From 2004 – 2011, he co-founded and managed Drug Delivery Solutions in Leatherhead, UK. It was also during this time he co-founded and seated as the senior scientific advisor to the MC2 Biotek Group, Denmark.\r\n\r\nDr. Steen was a professor of Oral Maxillofacial Surgery at European University College in Dubai from 2011 to 2013.\r\n\r\nDr. Steen has published more than 85 peer reviewed scientific papers within the fields of dental implants, bone grafting and reconstruction of facial malformations. He joins our team at Dr. Michael’s Dental Clinic with many years of private practice focusing on dental and maxillofacial implantology, bone grafting, reconstructive and orthognathic surgery.\r\n\r\n</div>','Prof. Steen Sindet-Pedersen','','publish','closed','closed','','prof-steen-sindet-pedersen','','','2015-02-15 15:28:24','2015-02-15 12:28:24','',0,'http://demo2.saitobaza.ru/?post_type=dentalist&#038;p=105',0,'dentalist','',0),
